#icon: VOP/mix
#context: sop
#type: node

= Point Mix qL =

*Version 0.2.0*

"""Blends point attributes between two inputs by an attribute."""

@Usage
    Connect the two geometries that you want to blend to the operator. Define a float attribute on one of the
    input geometries that will controll the mix, and set the _Control Attribute_ parameter to this.

@Limitations
    Currently it's only tested with point attributes of vector or float types. Further testing needed.

@Parameters
    Group:
        The group of points the operator affects.
    Attributes:
        List of attributes to mix.
    Envelope:
        A global multiplier of the effect.
    Control Attrib:
        Name of the attribute which controls the mix.
    Attrib On Second Input:
        Check this toggle if the control attribute is on the second input.

@Release_Notes
    Version 0.2.0:
        Supports arbitrary numbers of attributes.
    Version 0.1.0:
        Initial release.